Imágenes de ejemplo¶

In [5]:
category = "REAL"
category_path = os.path.join("test", category)
images = [f for f in os.listdir(category_path) if os.path.isfile(os.path.join(category_path, f))]

random_image_name = random.choice(images)
random_image_path = os.path.join(category_path, random_image_name)
img = plt.imread(random_image_path)
plt.imshow(img)
plt.title(f"Random Image: {category}/{random_image_name}")
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()
In [8]:
category = "FAKE"
category_path = os.path.join("test", category)

random_image_name = random.choice(images)
random_image_path = os.path.join(category_path, random_image_name)
img = plt.imread(random_image_path)
plt.imshow(img)
plt.title(f"Random Image: {category}/{random_image_name}")

IMG_SIZE = (128, 128)

base_model = tf.keras.applications.ResNet50(
    include_top=False,
    weights='imagenet',
    input_shape=IMG_SIZE + (3,)
)

base_model.trainable = True
for layer in base_model.layers[:-10]:
    layer.trainable = False
In [48]:
inputs = tf.keras.Input(shape=IMG_SIZE + (3,))
x = tf.keras.applications.resnet50.preprocess_input(inputs)
x = base_model(x, training=False)
x = tf.keras.layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D()(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)
x = tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)
outputs = tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

model = tf.keras.models.Model(inputs, outputs)

In [67]:
def predict_random_test_images_grid(
    model,
    base_test_path='test',
    num_images=10,
    cols=5,
    target_size=(32, 32)
):
    class_names = ['FAKE', 'REAL']

    # Recolectar todas las imgenes de TEST
    all_images = []
    for label_name in os.listdir(base_test_path):
        label_dir = os.path.join(base_test_path, label_name)
        if os.path.isdir(label_dir):
            for fname in os.listdir(label_dir):
                if fname.lower().endswith(('.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.bmp')):
                    all_images.append((os.path.join(label_dir, fname), label_name))

    if len(all_images) == 0:
        print("No se encontraron imgenes en", base_test_path)
        return

    num_images = min(len(all_images), num_images)
    selected_samples = random.sample(all_images, num_images)

    rows = math.ceil(num_images / cols)
    plt.figure(figsize=(3 * cols, 3.5 * rows))

    for i, (img_path, real_label_str) in enumerate(selected_samples):
        # Cargar y preprocesar
        img = tf.keras.utils.load_img(img_path, target_size=target_size)
        img_arr = tf.keras.utils.img_to_array(img)
        img_norm = img_arr / 255.0
        img_batch = np.expand_dims(img_norm, axis=0)

        # Prediccin (salida sigmoid)
        pred_score = model.predict(img_batch, verbose=0)[0][0]

        predicted_idx = 1 if pred_score > 0.5 else 0
        predicted_label = class_names[predicted_idx]

        real_label = real_label_str.upper()
        confidence = pred_score if predicted_idx == 1 else (1 - pred_score)

        plt.subplot(rows, cols, i + 1)
        plt.imshow(img)

        color = 'green' if real_label == predicted_label else 'red'
        plt.title(
            f"Real: {real_label}\nPred: {predicted_label}\nConf: {confidence:.2f}",
            color=color,
            fontsize=9
        )
        plt.axis('off')


    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

predict_random_test_images_grid(model, base_test_path='test', num_images=16, cols=4, target_size=(128, 128))
